theorem Topology.interior_image_interior_subset_closure_image
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y}
    (hf : Continuous f) {A : Set X} :
    interior (f '' interior A) ⊆ closure (f '' A) := by
  -- First, `interior S ⊆ closure S` for any set `S`.
  have h₁ : interior (f '' interior A) ⊆ closure (f '' interior A) :=
    interior_subset
  -- Next, apply the previously proven lemma about closures of images.
  have h₂ :
      closure (f '' interior A) ⊆ closure (f '' A) :=
    Topology.closure_image_interior_subset (X := X) (Y := Y)
      (f := f) hf (A := A)
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain the result.
  exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.image_interior_subset_closure_image
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {f : X → Y} {A : Set X} :
    interior (f '' interior A) ⊆ closure (f '' interior A) := by
  exact
    (interior_subset : interior (f '' interior A) ⊆ (f '' interior A))
      ▸ subset_closure

theorem Topology.image_closure_subset_closure_image
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {A : Set X} :
    f '' closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (f '' A) := by
  intro y hy
  rcases hy with ⟨x, hx_cl, rfl⟩
  -- We will show that `f x` belongs to the closure of `f '' A`.
  have : f x ∈ closure (f '' A) := by
    -- Use the neighbourhood characterisation of the closure.
    apply (mem_closure_iff).2
    intro V hV_open hxV
    -- The preimage of `V` under `f` is an open neighbourhood of `x`.
    have hU_open : IsOpen (f ⁻¹' V) := hV_open.preimage hf
    have hxU : x ∈ f ⁻¹' V := by
      simpa using hxV
    -- Because `x` is in the closure of `A`, this neighbourhood meets `A`.
    have h_nonempty : ((f ⁻¹' V) ∩ A).Nonempty := by
      have h_closure := (mem_closure_iff).1 hx_cl
      have h := h_closure (f ⁻¹' V) hU_open hxU
      simpa [Set.inter_comm] using h
    -- Map a witness through `f` to get a point of `(V ∩ f '' A)`.
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨z, hz_mem⟩
    have hzU : z ∈ f ⁻¹' V := hz_mem.1
    have hzA : z ∈ A := hz_mem.2
    have hzV : f z ∈ V := by
      simpa using hzU
    have hz_image : f z ∈ f '' A := ⟨z, hzA, rfl⟩
    exact ⟨f z, And.intro hzV hz_image⟩
  simpa using this

theorem Topology.image_interior_subset_closure_image
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y} {A : Set X} :
    f '' interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (f '' A) := by
  intro y hy
  rcases hy with ⟨x, hx_int, rfl⟩
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ (A : Set X) := interior_subset hx_int
  have h_im : (f x) ∈ f '' (A : Set X) := ⟨x, hxA, rfl⟩
  exact subset_closure h_im
